==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Brilliantine
<hw>Bril"lian*tine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>brillantine</ets>. See lst <er>Brilliant</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>An oily composition used to make the hair manageable and
glossy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A dress fabric having a glossy finish on both sides,
resembling alpaca but of superior quality.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brilliantly</ent>⟦br⟧
